  "description": "The (2,5) cinquefoil torus knot has a five-pointed star winding geometry — the highest pqScale of any common torus knot at 0.976, meaning coupling asymmetry is nearly at its maximum. macroKnot=0.65 nudges the matrix beyond the Torus endpoint toward Solomon, creating a topology that carries cinquefoil geometry into a two-ring reading. Sine strands let the winding structure be the entire sound. Slow LFO on braid depth pulls the sound across the WEAVE-I threshold on each cycle — each breath is a topology crossing.",
